// Unit 26 — Maatschappij & Cultuur
// Advanced Conjunctions & Essay Structure

export default {n:26,lang:"nl",srcLang:"en",track:"v2",title:"Maatschappij & Cultuur",sub:"Advanced Conjunctions & Essay Structure",icon:"🏛️",level:"B2.2",color:"#7B5EE8",lessons:[
  {id:"v2u26l1",title:"Maatschappelijke Thema's",icon:"🏙️",xp:40,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"Maatschappelijke Thema's",desc:"In deze les leer je belangrijke woorden over de Nederlandse maatschappij: gezondheidszorg, onderwijs, woningmarkt, beleid en meer.",goals:["Kernvocabulaire over maatschappelijke thema's","Praten over beleid en burgerschap","Maatschappelijke problemen bespreken"]},
        {type:"teach",trg:"de gezondheidszorg",src:"healthcare",pos:"noun",gender:"c",phonetic:"guh-ZONT-hytes-zorg",note:"Compound noun: gezondheid (health) + zorg (care)",example:"A: Hoe vind je de gezondheidszorg in Nederland?\nB: Over het algemeen is die goed georganiseerd.\nA: Maar de wachttijden zijn soms lang, toch?\nB: Ja, dat is een bekend probleem.\nA: Toch is het systeem betaalbaar voor iedereen.\nB: Dat klopt, daar mogen we blij mee zijn.",exampleSrc:"A: How do you find healthcare in the Netherlands?\nB: Generally it's well organized.\nA: But waiting times are sometimes long, right?\nB: Yes, that's a well-known problem.\nA: Still, the system is affordable for everyone.\nB: That's true, we can be happy about that.",funFact:"A de-word (common gender). About 2/3 of Dutch nouns use 'de'. All plurals always use 'de'."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"het onderwijs",src:"education",pos:"noun",gender:"n",phonetic:"ON-dur-wice",note:"het article. Covers all levels from basisschool to universiteit.",example:"A: Het Nederlandse onderwijs staat internationaal hoog aangeschreven.\nB: Dat wist ik niet. Waarom eigenlijk?\nA: Er is veel aandacht voor zelfstandig leren.\nB: En hoe zit het met de kosten?\nA: Universiteiten zijn relatief betaalbaar.\nB: Interessant, dat verschilt echt per land.",exampleSrc:"A: Dutch education is highly regarded internationally.\nB: I didn't know that. Why exactly?\nA: There is a lot of focus on independent learning.\nB: And what about the costs?\nA: Universities are relatively affordable.\nB: Interesting, that really differs per country.",funFact:"A het-word (neuter). About 1/3 of Dutch nouns use 'het'. No reliable rule, learn it with the word."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"de woningmarkt",src:"housing market",pos:"noun",gender:"c",phonetic:"WOH-ning-markt",note:"Compound: woning (dwelling) + markt (market). A hot topic in NL.",example:"A: De woningmarkt in Nederland is echt overspannen.\nB: Ja, de prijzen zijn enorm gestegen.\nA: Vooral voor starters is het bijna onmogelijk.\nB: De overheid probeert wel maatregelen te nemen.\nA: Maar tot nu toe helpt het niet genoeg.\nB: Nee, er moeten meer huizen gebouwd worden.",exampleSrc:"A: The housing market in the Netherlands is really overheated.\nB: Yes, prices have risen enormously.\nA: Especially for first-time buyers it's almost impossible.\nB: The government is trying to take measures.\nA: But so far it's not helping enough.\nB: No, more houses need to be built.",funFact:"A de-word (common gender). About 2/3 of Dutch nouns use 'de'. All plurals always use 'de'."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"het beleid",src:"policy",pos:"noun",gender:"n",phonetic:"buh-LITE",note:"het article. Used in compounds: klimaatbeleid, onderwijsbeleid, etc.",example:"A: Wat vind je van het huidige klimaatbeleid?\nB: Ik denk dat het ambitieuzer moet.\nA: De overheid heeft wel doelen gesteld.\nB: Ja, maar het beleid wordt niet altijd goed uitgevoerd.\nA: Dat is een probleem bij veel beleidsplannen.\nB: Precies, de uitvoering is net zo belangrijk.",exampleSrc:"A: What do you think of the current climate policy?\nB: I think it needs to be more ambitious.\nA: The government has set goals.\nB: Yes, but the policy isn't always implemented well.\nA: That's a problem with many policy plans.\nB: Exactly, the execution is just as important.",funFact:"A het-word (neuter). About 1/3 of Dutch nouns use 'het'. No reliable rule, learn it with the word."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"de burger",src:"citizen",pos:"noun",gender:"c",phonetic:"BUR-gur",note:"Also means hamburger in informal Dutch. Context makes it clear.",example:"A: Elke burger heeft rechten en plichten.\nB: Ja, dat hoort bij het leven in een democratie.\nA: Zoals stemrecht en belasting betalen.\nB: Vind je dat burgers genoeg inspraak hebben?\nA: Soms wel, soms niet. Het hangt van het onderwerp af.\nB: Burgerparticipatie wordt steeds belangrijker.",exampleSrc:"A: Every citizen has rights and duties.\nB: Yes, that's part of living in a democracy.\nA: Like the right to vote and paying taxes.\nB: Do you think citizens have enough say?\nA: Sometimes yes, sometimes no. It depends on the topic.\nB: Citizen participation is becoming increasingly important.",funFact:"A de-word (common gender). About 2/3 of Dutch nouns use 'de'. All plurals always use 'de'."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"de samenleving",src:"society",pos:"noun",gender:"c",phonetic:"SAH-men-lay-ving",note:"samen (together) + leving (living). Core concept for this unit.",example:"A: De Nederlandse samenleving is heel divers.\nB: Dat klopt, er wonen mensen uit de hele wereld.\nA: Hoe gaan mensen met die diversiteit om?\nB: Over het algemeen vrij goed, denk ik.\nA: Er zijn natuurlijk ook spanningen.\nB: Ja, maar de samenleving past zich steeds aan.",exampleSrc:"A: Dutch society is very diverse.\nB: That's true, people from all over the world live here.\nA: How do people deal with that diversity?\nB: Generally quite well, I think.\nA: There are of course also tensions.\nB: Yes, but society keeps adapting.",funFact:"A de-word (common gender). About 2/3 of Dutch nouns use 'de'. All plurals always use 'de'."},
        {type:"tip",title:"Maatschappelijke woordenschat",deepDive:"Compound nouns are central to Dutch. The last part determines the article:\n\nde gezondheid + de zorg = de gezondheidszorg\nde woning + de markt = de woningmarkt\n\nSometimes a linking -s- or -en- appears between parts:\nbeleid + plan = beleidsplan (linking -s-)\nziek + huis = ziekenhuis (linking -en-)",text:"Dutch society vocabulary often uses compound nouns:\n\n- gezondheidszorg = gezondheid + zorg\n- woningmarkt = woning + markt\n- samenleving = samen + leving\n- burgerschap = burger + schap\n\nUnderstanding the parts helps you decode new compounds."},
        {type:"mc",q:"Welk woord betekent 'healthcare'?",opts:["de gezondheidszorg","het onderwijs","de woningmarkt","het beleid"],ans:"de gezondheidszorg",hint:"Think about gezondheid (health) + zorg (care)."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["burger","beleid","onderwijs","markt"],hint:"A person living in a country with rights and duties.",s:"Elke {1} heeft rechten en plichten in een democratie.",a:"burger"},
        {type:"mc",q:"De prijzen op de woningmarkt zijn enorm gestegen. Wat is 'de woningmarkt'?",opts:["the stock market","the housing market","the job market","the supermarket"],ans:"the housing market",hint:"Woning means dwelling or home."},
        {type:"match",pairs:[
          {trg:"de gezondheidszorg",src:"healthcare"},
          {trg:"het onderwijs",src:"education"},
          {trg:"de woningmarkt",src:"housing market"},
          {trg:"het beleid",src:"policy"},
          {trg:"de burger",src:"citizen"},
          {trg:"de samenleving",src:"society"}
        ]},
        {type:"fb",opts:["onderwijs","beleid","burger","zorg"],hint:"What do children receive at school? (het-word)",s:"Het Nederlandse {1} staat internationaal hoog aangeschreven.",a:"onderwijs"},
        {type:"mc",q:"'De samenleving past zich steeds aan.' Wat betekent 'samenleving'?",opts:["parliament","government","society","economy"],ans:"society",hint:"samen (together) + leving (living)."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"het vraagstuk",src:"issue, question (societal)",pos:"noun",gender:"n",phonetic:"VRAHG-stuk",note:"het article. More formal than 'probleem'. Used in policy discussions.",example:"A: De woningcrisis is een belangrijk maatschappelijk vraagstuk.\nB: Absoluut, het raakt miljoenen mensen.\nA: Welke vraagstukken vind jij het belangrijkst?\nB: Klimaatverandering en ongelijkheid.\nA: Dat zijn inderdaad urgente kwesties.\nB: De politiek moet daar meer aandacht aan besteden.",exampleSrc:"A: The housing crisis is an important societal issue.\nB: Absolutely, it affects millions of people.\nA: Which issues do you find most important?\nB: Climate change and inequality.\nA: Those are indeed urgent matters.\nB: Politicians need to pay more attention to those.",funFact:"A het-word (neuter). About 1/3 of Dutch nouns use 'het'. No reliable rule, learn it with the word."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["vraagstuk","burger","beleid","zorg"],hint:"A formal word for a societal issue or question.",s:"Klimaatverandering is een belangrijk maatschappelijk {1}.",a:"vraagstuk"},
        {type:"mc",q:"Which compound noun means 'housing market'?",opts:["huurmarkt","woningbouw","huizenprijs","woningmarkt"],ans:"woningmarkt",hint:"woning (dwelling) + markt (market)."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"The government must implement better policy to improve healthcare.",s:"De {1} moet beter {2} voeren om de {3} te verbeteren.",blanks:{"1":"overheid","2":"beleid","3":"gezondheidszorg"},pool:["overheid","beleid","gezondheidszorg","burger","onderwijs"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"'Burgerparticipatie wordt steeds belangrijker.' Wat is 'burgerparticipatie'?",opts:["citizen participation","burger restaurant","civil war","city planning"],ans:"citizen participation",hint:"___ + participatie = civic engagement (compound noun)"}
  ]},
  {id:"v2u26l2",title:"Doordat & Zodat",icon:"🔗",xp:40,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"Doordat & Zodat",desc:"Leer het verschil tussen doordat (because of the fact that) en zodat (so that). Beide zijn ondergeschikte voegwoorden die oorzaak en gevolg uitdrukken.",goals:["Doordat gebruiken voor oorzaak","Zodat gebruiken voor doel/gevolg","Het verschil tussen doordat en omdat begrijpen"]},
        {type:"teach",trg:"doordat",src:"because of the fact that, due to the fact that",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"Emphasizes external cause. Verb goes to END of doordat-clause.",example:"A: Waarom is het project mislukt?\nB: Doordat er te weinig budget was.\nA: Kon dat niet eerder worden opgelost?\nB: Nee, doordat de communicatie slecht was, wist niemand het.\nA: Dat is frustrerend.\nB: Ja, doordat meerdere dingen misgingen, was het onvermijdelijk.",exampleSrc:"A: Why did the project fail?\nB: Due to the fact that there was too little budget.\nA: Couldn't that have been resolved earlier?\nB: No, because communication was poor, nobody knew.\nA: That's frustrating.\nB: Yes, because multiple things went wrong, it was inevitable.",funFact:"Dutch verbs follow the stem + ending pattern. Find the stem, add the right ending."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"zodat",src:"so that, in order that",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"Expresses purpose or intended result. Verb to END of zodat-clause.",example:"A: Waarom leer je Nederlands?\nB: Zodat ik in Amsterdam kan werken.\nA: Slim! En je studeert elke dag?\nB: Ja, zodat ik snel vorderingen maak.\nA: Dat is bewonderenswaardig.\nB: Ik wil het goed doen, zodat mijn collega's mij begrijpen.",exampleSrc:"A: Why are you learning Dutch?\nB: So that I can work in Amsterdam.\nA: Smart! And you study every day?\nB: Yes, so that I make quick progress.\nA: That's admirable.\nB: I want to do it well, so that my colleagues understand me.",funFact:"Dutch verbs follow the stem + ending pattern. Find the stem, add the right ending."},
        {type:"tip",title:"Doordat vs. Omdat vs. Zodat",deepDive:"Doordat emphasizes that the cause is external or factual. Compare:\n\nDoordat het regende, werd het feest afgelast.\n(Because of the rain, the party was cancelled. External cause.)\n\nOmdat het regende, bleven we thuis.\n(Because it rained, we stayed home. Our choice.)\n\nZodat is always forward-looking (purpose):\nIk studeer hard zodat ik slaag.\n(I study hard so that I pass.)",text:"All three connect clauses, but differently:\n\n- doordat: external cause (something happened BECAUSE of X)\n- omdat: reason/motivation (I did it BECAUSE of reason)\n- zodat: purpose/result (I did it SO THAT Y happens)\n\nDoordat = cause you observe\nOmdat = reason you choose\nZodat = goal you aim for"},
        {type:"mc",q:"'___ er te weinig budget was, is het project mislukt.' Welk voegwoord past hier?",opts:["Doordat","Zodat","Hoewel","Mits"],ans:"Doordat",hint:"The budget shortage was an external cause of failure."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["zodat","doordat","omdat","mits"],hint:"You're expressing a purpose or goal.",s:"Ik leer elke dag Nederlands {1} ik vlot kan communiceren.",a:"zodat"},
        {type:"mc",q:"Which conjunction expresses PURPOSE?",opts:["doordat","zodat","omdat","tenzij"],ans:"zodat",hint:"Think about 'so that' something will happen."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"het gevolg",src:"consequence, result",pos:"noun",gender:"n",phonetic:"guh-VOLG",note:"het article. Plural: gevolgen. Common in formal/news Dutch.",example:"A: Wat zijn de gevolgen van de woningcrisis?\nB: Veel jongeren kunnen geen huis kopen.\nA: Dat heeft ook gevolgen voor de economie.\nB: Ja, doordat mensen niet verhuizen, stagneert de markt.\nA: En het gevolg is dat de huurprijzen stijgen.\nB: Precies, het is een vicieuze cirkel.",exampleSrc:"A: What are the consequences of the housing crisis?\nB: Many young people can't buy a house.\nA: That also has consequences for the economy.\nB: Yes, because people don't move, the market stagnates.\nA: And the consequence is that rental prices rise.\nB: Exactly, it's a vicious circle.",funFact:"A het-word (neuter). About 1/3 of Dutch nouns use 'het'. No reliable rule, learn it with the word."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"de oorzaak",src:"cause, reason",pos:"noun",gender:"c",phonetic:"OOR-zahk",note:"de article. Plural: oorzaken. Pairs naturally with gevolg.",example:"A: Wat is de oorzaak van de stijgende huizenprijzen?\nB: Er zijn meerdere oorzaken.\nA: Zoals een tekort aan nieuwbouw?\nB: Ja, en doordat de rente lang laag was.\nA: De oorzaken zijn dus zowel economisch als politiek.\nB: Precies, het is een complex probleem.",exampleSrc:"A: What is the cause of rising house prices?\nB: There are multiple causes.\nA: Such as a shortage of new construction?\nB: Yes, and because interest rates were low for a long time.\nA: So the causes are both economic and political.\nB: Exactly, it's a complex problem.",funFact:"A de-word (common gender). About 2/3 of Dutch nouns use 'de'. All plurals always use 'de'."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["Doordat","Zodat","Hoewel","Mits"],hint:"Something outside your control led to the problem worsening.",s:"{1} de overheid niet ingreep, werd het probleem erger.",a:"Doordat"},
        {type:"mc",q:"'Ze verhuisde naar Utrecht ___ ze dichter bij haar werk kon wonen.'",opts:["tenzij","doordat","zodat","ofschoon"],ans:"zodat",hint:"She moved with a specific purpose in mind."},
        {type:"match",pairs:[{trg:"doordat",src:"because of the fact that"},{trg:"zodat",src:"so that"},{trg:"omdat",src:"because (reason)"},{trg:"het gevolg",src:"consequence"},{trg:"de oorzaak",src:"cause"}]},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"First blank: external cause. Second blank: resulting consequence.",s:"{1} de rente laag was, konden meer mensen lenen, {2} de huizenprijzen stegen.",blanks:{"1":"Doordat","2":"zodat"},pool:["Doordat","zodat","mits","hoewel"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"'Doordat de communicatie slecht was, wist niemand het.' What does doordat emphasize?",opts:["A condition","A personal choice","A purpose","An external cause"],ans:"An external cause",hint:"Which conjunction points to an ___ factor?"},
        {type:"fb",opts:["gevolg","oorzaak","beleid","vraagstuk"],hint:"The opposite of 'oorzaak': what is the result?",s:"Het {1} van slecht beleid is dat burgers het vertrouwen verliezen.",a:"gevolg"},
        {type:"mc",q:"Welke zin is correct?",opts:["Doordat het hard regende, werd de wedstrijd afgelast.","Zodat het hard regende, werd de wedstrijd afgelast.","Mits het hard regende, werd de wedstrijd afgelast.","Tenzij het hard regende, werd de wedstrijd afgelast."],ans:"Doordat het hard regende, werd de wedstrijd afgelast.",hint:"Rain was an outside factor that led to cancellation."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["zodat","doordat","mits","tenzij"],hint:"The investment has a specific purpose for student learning.",s:"De school investeert in technologie, {1} leerlingen beter leren.",a:"zodat"},
        {type:"mc",q:"'De oorzaak van het probleem is slecht beleid.' Wat betekent 'oorzaak'?",opts:["consequence","cause","solution","question"],ans:"cause",hint:"This conjunction expresses what: reason, contrast, or result?"}
  ]},
  {id:"v2u26l3",title:"Mits, Tenzij, Hoewel",icon:"⚖️",xp:40,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"Mits, Tenzij, Hoewel",desc:"Drie krachtige voegwoorden: mits (provided that), tenzij (unless), en hoewel (although). Essentieel voor genuanceerd argumenteren.",goals:["Mits voor voorwaarden gebruiken","Tenzij voor uitzonderingen","Hoewel voor tegenstellingen"]},
        {type:"teach",trg:"mits",src:"provided that, on condition that",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"Formal. Sets a positive condition. Verb to END.",example:"A: Mag ik eerder naar huis vandaag?\nB: Ja, mits je je werk af hebt.\nA: Natuurlijk, ik ben bijna klaar.\nB: Prima. Je mag ook thuiswerken, mits je bereikbaar blijft.\nA: Dat is een goede regeling.\nB: We zijn flexibel, mits de resultaten goed zijn.",exampleSrc:"A: Can I go home early today?\nB: Yes, provided that you've finished your work.\nA: Of course, I'm almost done.\nB: Fine. You can also work from home, provided you remain reachable.\nA: That's a good arrangement.\nB: We're flexible, provided the results are good.",funFact:"Dutch verbs follow the stem + ending pattern. Find the stem, add the right ending."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"tenzij",src:"unless",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"Sets a negative condition (exception). Verb to END.",example:"A: Gaat het evenement door?\nB: Ja, tenzij het gaat stormen.\nA: En als er te weinig aanmeldingen zijn?\nB: Dan gaat het ook door, tenzij er minder dan tien mensen komen.\nA: Dat klinkt redelijk.\nB: We annuleren nooit, tenzij het echt niet anders kan.",exampleSrc:"A: Is the event going ahead?\nB: Yes, unless there's going to be a storm.\nA: And if there are too few registrations?\nB: Then it still goes ahead, unless fewer than ten people come.\nA: That sounds reasonable.\nB: We never cancel, unless there's really no other option.",funFact:"Dutch verbs follow the stem + ending pattern. Find the stem, add the right ending."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"hoewel",src:"although, even though",pos:"conj",gender:null,note:"Concessive: acknowledges X but asserts Y anyway. Formal register.",example:"A: Hoewel het regent, ga ik toch fietsen.\nB: Echt waar? Je wordt drijfnat!\nA: Hoewel dat klopt, vind ik het niet erg.\nB: Je bent een echte Nederlander geworden!\nA: Hoewel ik hier pas twee jaar woon, voel ik me thuis.\nB: Dat is mooi om te horen.",exampleSrc:"A: Although it's raining, I'm still going cycling.\nB: Really? You'll get soaking wet!\nA: Although that's true, I don't mind.\nB: You've become a true Dutchman!\nA: Although I've only lived here two years, I feel at home.\nB: That's nice to hear.",funFact:"Word order matters: some conjunctions keep normal order, others push the verb to the end."},
        {type:"tip",title:"Voorwaardelijk vs. Toegevend",deepDive:"Compare the logic:\n\nMits je studeert, slaag je. (If you study, you pass.)\nTenzij je studeert, zak je. (Unless you study, you fail.)\nHoewel je studeert, is het moeilijk. (Although you study, it's hard.)\n\nMits and tenzij are mirrors:\nmits = positive gate (condition must be met)\ntenzij = negative gate (exception that blocks)\n\nHoewel stands apart: it concedes a point but doesn't change the main claim.",text:"These conjunctions serve different logical functions:\n\n- mits: positive condition (X happens IF Y is true)\n- tenzij: negative condition (X happens UNLESS Y is true)\n- hoewel: concession (X happens DESPITE Y being true)\n\nAll three send the verb to the END of their clause."},
        {type:"mc",q:"'Je mag eerder weg, ___ je je werk af hebt.' Welk voegwoord?",opts:["mits","tenzij","hoewel","doordat"],ans:"mits",hint:"A positive condition must be met first."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["tenzij","mits","hoewel","zodat"],hint:"The party continues unless one condition is met.",s:"Het feest gaat door, {1} het gaat stormen.",a:"tenzij"},
        {type:"mc",q:"'___ het moeilijk is, geef ik niet op.' Which conjunction fits?",opts:["Mits","Hoewel","Tenzij","Doordat"],ans:"Hoewel",hint:"You acknowledge difficulty but persist anyway."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"ofschoon",src:"although, albeit (formal)",pos:"part",gender:null,note:"Very formal synonym of hoewel. Used in written/academic Dutch.",example:"A: Ofschoon de economie groeit, neemt de ongelijkheid toe.\nB: Dat is een verontrustende trend.\nA: Ofschoon er maatregelen worden genomen, is het niet genoeg.\nB: Welke oplossingen zie jij?\nA: Ofschoon het ingewikkeld is, moeten we het belastingstelsel hervormen.\nB: Daar ben ik het mee eens.",exampleSrc:"A: Although the economy is growing, inequality is increasing.\nB: That's a worrying trend.\nA: Although measures are being taken, it's not enough.\nB: What solutions do you see?\nA: Although it's complicated, we must reform the tax system.\nB: I agree with that.",funFact:"Dutch and English are the closest major language pair in the world. Many words share common roots."},
        {type:"match",pairs:[{trg:"mits",src:"provided that"},{trg:"tenzij",src:"unless"},{trg:"hoewel",src:"although"},{trg:"doordat",src:"because of"},{trg:"zodat",src:"so that"}]},
        {type:"fb",opts:["Hoewel","Mits","Tenzij","Doordat"],hint:"Acknowledging a fact while asserting something contrasting.",s:"{1} Nederland een klein land is, heeft het veel internationale invloed.",a:"Hoewel"},
        {type:"mc",q:"Which conjunction sets a NEGATIVE condition (an exception)?",opts:["hoewel","mits","tenzij","zodat"],ans:"tenzij",hint:"Think of 'unless' in English."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Although measures are taken, the problem isn't solved, because the causes run deeper.",s:"{1} de overheid maatregelen neemt, {2} het probleem niet opgelost, {3} de oorzaken dieper liggen.",blanks:{"1":"Hoewel","2":"wordt","3":"doordat"},pool:["Hoewel","wordt","doordat","mits","tenzij"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"'Ofschoon' is een formeel synoniem van welk woord?",opts:["zodat","mits","tenzij","hoewel"],ans:"hoewel",hint:"Both express concession (although/even though)."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["mits","tenzij","hoewel","doordat"],hint:"The discount requires meeting a condition.",s:"Je krijgt korting, {1} je een studentenkaart hebt.",a:"mits"},
        {type:"mc",q:"'Mits het droog blijft, gaan we picknicken.' What does 'mits' express?",opts:["A positive condition (provided that)","A negative condition (unless)","A contrast (although)","A cause (because)"],ans:"A positive condition (provided that)",hint:"A ___ ___al: on the ___ that something good happens"},
        {type:"fb",opts:["Hoewel","Mits","Doordat","Zodat"],hint:"Acknowledging disagreement while showing respect.",s:"{1} ik het er niet mee eens ben, respecteer ik je mening.",a:"Hoewel"},
        {type:"mc",q:"'We gaan door, tenzij er onvoldoende aanmeldingen zijn.' What would cancel the event?",opts:["Good weather","Not enough registrations","Too many registrations","A positive condition"],ans:"Not enough registrations",hint:"Which conjunction introduces an exception that stops the plan?"}
  ]},
  {id:"v2u26l4",title:"Naarmate & Hoe...hoe",icon:"📈",xp:40,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"Naarmate & Hoe...hoe",desc:"Leer proportionele constructies: naarmate (as/the more that) en hoe...hoe (the more...the more). Perfect voor het beschrijven van trends en verbanden.",goals:["Naarmate-zinnen bouwen","Hoe...hoe-constructies gebruiken","Trends en verhoudingen beschrijven"]},
        {type:"teach",trg:"naarmate",src:"as, in proportion as, the more that",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"Formal. Expresses proportional change. Verb to END of naarmate-clause.",example:"A: Naarmate je langer in Nederland woont, spreek je beter Nederlands.\nB: Dat merk ik inderdaad.\nA: Naarmate je meer oefent, wordt het makkelijker.\nB: En naarmate je meer mensen ontmoet, groeit je woordenschat.\nA: Precies! Het gaat steeds sneller.\nB: Naarmate ik meer leer, wil ik ook meer weten.",exampleSrc:"A: The longer you live in the Netherlands, the better you speak Dutch.\nB: I do notice that indeed.\nA: The more you practice, the easier it gets.\nB: And the more people you meet, the more your vocabulary grows.\nA: Exactly! It keeps getting faster.\nB: The more I learn, the more I want to know.",funFact:"Dutch verbs follow the stem + ending pattern. Find the stem, add the right ending."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"hoe...hoe",src:"the more...the more",pos:"part",gender:null,note:"Two hoe-clauses. Each starts with hoe + comparative. Very common pattern.",example:"A: Hoe meer je leest, hoe beter je schrijft.\nB: Dat is een goed advies.\nA: Hoe eerder je begint, hoe meer tijd je hebt.\nB: En hoe vaker je oefent, hoe zelfverzekerder je wordt.\nA: Hoe langer ik hier woon, hoe meer ik van Nederland houd.\nB: Dat hoor ik graag!",exampleSrc:"A: The more you read, the better you write.\nB: That's good advice.\nA: The earlier you start, the more time you have.\nB: And the more often you practice, the more confident you become.\nA: The longer I live here, the more I love the Netherlands.\nB: I'm happy to hear that!",funFact:"Dutch and English are the closest major language pair in the world. Many words share common roots."},
        {type:"tip",title:"Proportionele constructies",deepDive:"Word order differences:\n\nNaarmate: verb goes to END of naarmate-clause, main clause has normal V2:\nNaarmate je meer oefent, wordt het makkelijker.\n\nHoe...hoe: both clauses have the comparative after hoe, verb at end:\nHoe meer je oefent, hoe makkelijker het wordt.\n\nNaarmate is more formal/written. Hoe...hoe is common in speech too.",text:"Both express 'the more X, the more Y':\n\n- naarmate: formal, one clause starts with naarmate\n  Naarmate je ouder wordt, word je wijzer.\n\n- hoe...hoe: two parallel hoe-clauses\n  Hoe ouder je wordt, hoe wijzer je bent.\n\nBoth use comparatives (meer, beter, langer, etc.)."},
        {type:"mc",q:"'___ je langer studeert, ___ beter word je.' Welke constructie?",opts:["Hoe...hoe","Naarmate...des","Mits...dan","Tenzij...anders"],ans:"Hoe...hoe",hint:"Two parallel clauses with comparatives."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["Naarmate","Hoewel","Tenzij","Doordat"],hint:"In proportion as the economy grows, employment increases.",s:"{1} de economie groeit, neemt de werkgelegenheid toe.",a:"Naarmate"},
        {type:"mc",q:"Which construction is MORE formal?",opts:["hoe...hoe","naarmate","doordat","zodat"],ans:"naarmate",hint:"One of these proportional constructions belongs to written/formal Dutch."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["makkelijker","moeilijk","goed","snel"],hint:"The second hoe needs a comparative form meaning 'easier'.",s:"Hoe meer je oefent, hoe {1} het wordt.",a:"makkelijker"},
        {type:"teach",trg:"des te",src:"all the more (formal)",pos:"part",gender:null,note:"Very formal. Often paired with naarmate. Des te + comparative.",example:"A: Naarmate de bevolking groeit, worden de steden des te drukker.\nB: Dat is een logisch gevolg.\nA: En des te meer woningen zijn er nodig.\nB: De druk op de woningmarkt wordt des te groter.\nA: Precies, naarmate er meer mensen komen.\nB: Het is een uitdaging voor de hele samenleving.",exampleSrc:"A: As the population grows, cities become all the more crowded.\nB: That's a logical consequence.\nA: And all the more housing is needed.\nB: The pressure on the housing market becomes all the greater.\nA: Exactly, as more people arrive.\nB: It's a challenge for all of society.",funFact:"Dutch and English are the closest major language pair in the world. Many words share common roots."},
        {type:"match",pairs:[{trg:"naarmate",src:"as / in proportion as"},{trg:"hoe...hoe",src:"the more...the more"},{trg:"des te",src:"all the more"},{trg:"mits",src:"provided that"},{trg:"tenzij",src:"unless"}]},
        {type:"mc",q:"'Naarmate de temperatuur stijgt, smelten de ijskappen des te sneller.' Wat betekent 'des te'?",opts:["despite that","less and less","all the more","because of that"],ans:"all the more",hint:"It intensifies the comparative that follows."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"The more you learn about Dutch society, the better you understand the culture.",s:"{1} meer je leert over de Nederlandse {2}, {3} beter begrijp je de cultuur.",blanks:{"1":"Hoe","2":"samenleving","3":"hoe"},pool:["Hoe","samenleving","hoe","Naarmate","beleid"]},
        {type:"fb",opts:["Naarmate","Hoewel","Tenzij","Zodat"],hint:"As you get older, you become all the wiser. Formal style.",s:"{1} je ouder wordt, word je des te wijzer.",a:"Naarmate"},
        {type:"mc",q:"Welke zin gebruikt hoe...hoe correct?",opts:["Hoe vaker je oefent, doordat je beter wordt.","Hoe vaker je oefent, mits je beter wordt.","Hoe vaker je oefent, tenzij je beter wordt.","Hoe vaker je oefent, hoe beter je wordt."],ans:"Hoe vaker je oefent, hoe beter je wordt.",hint:"Both halves of this construction start the same way."},
        {type:"mc",q:"'Naarmate de stad groeit, wordt de woningmarkt krapper.' What does naarmate express?",opts:["A proportional relationship","A contradiction","A condition","A purpose"],ans:"A proportional relationship",hint:"As one thing increases, the other changes ___ly."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["gezondheidszorg","woningmarkt","samenleving","oorzaak"],hint:"Healthcare waiting times affect citizen satisfaction.",s:"Hoe langer de wachttijd bij de {1}, hoe ontevredener de burgers worden.",a:"gezondheidszorg"},
        {type:"mc",q:"Which sentence is correct?",opts:["Naarmate de bevolking groeit, de woningnood stijgt.","Naarmate de bevolking groeit, stijgt de woningnood.","De bevolking groeit naarmate stijgt de woningnood.","Stijgt de woningnood naarmate de bevolking groeit."],ans:"Naarmate de bevolking groeit, stijgt de woningnood.",hint:"Proportional clause first (verb final), then main clause with inversion."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["mensen","beleid","oorzaak","gevolg"],hint:"Proportional conjunction: as more _____ come...",s:"Hoe meer {1} er komen, hoe drukker de woningmarkt wordt.",a:"mensen"}
  ]},
  {id:"v2u26l5",title:"Standpunten Formuleren",icon:"📝",xp:40,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"Standpunten Formuleren",desc:"Leer je mening gestructureerd presenteren met signaalwoorden: ten eerste, daarnaast, bovendien, tot slot. Essentieel voor essays en presentaties.",goals:["Argumenten structureren met signaalwoorden","Standpunten helder formuleren","Formeel betogen in het Nederlands"]},
        {type:"teach",trg:"ten eerste",src:"firstly, in the first place",pos:"intj",gender:null,note:"Opens the first argument. Often followed by ten tweede, ten derde.",example:"A: Waarom ben je voor meer fietsinfrastructuur?\nB: Ten eerste is fietsen gezond.\nA: Dat is een goed punt. Nog meer redenen?\nB: Ten eerste de gezondheid, ten tweede het milieu.\nA: En economisch?\nB: Ten eerste bespaart het geld op brandstof.",exampleSrc:"A: Why are you in favor of more cycling infrastructure?\nB: Firstly, cycling is healthy.\nA: That's a good point. More reasons?\nB: Firstly health, secondly the environment.\nA: And economically?\nB: Firstly, it saves money on fuel.",funFact:"Dutch and English are the closest major language pair in the world. Many words share common roots."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"daarnaast",src:"moreover, in addition, besides that",pos:"noun",gender:null,note:"Adds a parallel argument. Less formal than bovendien.",example:"A: Fietsen is goed voor je gezondheid. Daarnaast is het goed voor het milieu.\nB: Dat klopt. Zijn er nog meer voordelen?\nA: Daarnaast bespaar je geld op benzine.\nB: En daarnaast is het ook gewoon leuk.\nA: Daarnaast verbetert het de verkeerssituatie.\nB: Je hebt me overtuigd!",exampleSrc:"A: Cycling is good for your health. Moreover, it's good for the environment.\nB: That's true. Are there more advantages?\nA: In addition, you save money on fuel.\nB: And besides that, it's also just fun.\nA: Moreover, it improves the traffic situation.\nB: You've convinced me!",funFact:"Dutch and English are the closest major language pair in the world. Many words share common roots."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"bovendien",src:"furthermore, moreover (formal)",pos:"verb",gender:null,note:"Adds a STRONGER supporting argument. More formal than daarnaast.",example:"A: De gezondheidszorg moet hervormd worden.\nB: Waarom vind je dat?\nA: De wachttijden zijn te lang. Bovendien stijgen de kosten elk jaar.\nB: Bovendien is er een tekort aan personeel.\nA: Precies. Bovendien is de kwaliteit ongelijk verdeeld.\nB: Het systeem heeft inderdaad meerdere problemen.",exampleSrc:"A: Healthcare needs to be reformed.\nB: Why do you think that?\nA: Waiting times are too long. Furthermore, costs rise every year.\nB: Furthermore, there's a staff shortage.\nA: Exactly. Moreover, quality is unevenly distributed.\nB: The system does indeed have multiple problems.",funFact:"Dutch verbs follow the stem + ending pattern. Find the stem, add the right ending."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"tot slot",src:"finally, in conclusion",pos:"intj",gender:null,note:"Signals the final argument or conclusion. Very common in essays.",example:"A: Je hebt drie argumenten genoemd. Wil je afsluiten?\nB: Ja. Tot slot wil ik benadrukken dat actie nodig is.\nA: Dat is een krachtige afsluiting.\nB: Tot slot moeten we niet vergeten dat het om mensen gaat.\nA: Goed gezegd.\nB: Tot slot: de tijd voor verandering is nu.",exampleSrc:"A: You've mentioned three arguments. Do you want to wrap up?\nB: Yes. Finally, I want to emphasize that action is needed.\nA: That's a powerful conclusion.\nB: Finally, we must not forget that it's about people.\nA: Well said.\nB: In conclusion: the time for change is now.",funFact:"Dutch and English are the closest major language pair in the world. Many words share common roots."},
        {type:"tip",title:"Argumentstructuur",deepDive:"Dutch argumentation style values directness and structure. Unlike some cultures where the main point comes last, Dutch essays often state the thesis FIRST, then support it:\n\nStelling (thesis): Fietsen moet gestimuleerd worden.\nTen eerste is het gezond.\nDaarnaast is het milieuvriendelijk.\nBovendien bespaart het kosten.\nTot slot verbetert het de leefbaarheid.",text:"A well-structured Dutch argument follows this pattern:\n\n1. ten eerste... (first argument)\n2. daarnaast / ten tweede... (additional argument)\n3. bovendien... (stronger supporting argument)\n4. tot slot... (final point / conclusion)\n\nThis creates a clear, logical flow that is valued in Dutch academic and professional writing."},
        {type:"mc",q:"Welk signaalwoord gebruik je om je EERSTE argument te introduceren?",opts:["ten eerste","daarnaast","bovendien","tot slot"],ans:"ten eerste",hint:"This signals the beginning of your argument chain."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["Ten eerste","Bovendien","Tot slot","Hoewel"],hint:"This word opens the first argument.",s:"{1} is fietsen gezond. Daarnaast is het milieuvriendelijk.",a:"Ten eerste"},
        {type:"mc",q:"Which word adds the STRONGEST additional argument?",opts:["daarnaast","bovendien","ten eerste","tot slot"],ans:"bovendien",hint:"More formal and emphatic than 'daarnaast'."},
        {type:"match",pairs:[
          {trg:"ten eerste",src:"firstly"},
          {trg:"daarnaast",src:"moreover / in addition"},
          {trg:"bovendien",src:"furthermore (formal)"},
          {trg:"tot slot",src:"finally / in conclusion"},
          {trg:"ten tweede",src:"secondly"}
        ]},
        {type:"fb",opts:["Bovendien","Ten eerste","Tot slot","Tenzij"],hint:"Adding a strong additional argument about staffing.",s:"De kosten zijn hoog. {1} is er een personeelstekort.",a:"Bovendien"},
        {type:"mc",q:"'___ wil ik benadrukken dat verandering nodig is.' Welk signaalwoord sluit het betoog af?",opts:["Daarnaast","Ten eerste","Tot slot","Bovendien"],ans:"Tot slot",hint:"This signals the final point."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Structure: first point, additional point, final point.",s:"{1} is onderwijs belangrijk. {2} bevordert het gelijkheid. {3} is het een investering in de toekomst.",blanks:{"1":"Ten eerste","2":"Daarnaast","3":"Tot slot"},pool:["Ten eerste","Daarnaast","Tot slot","Hoewel","Doordat"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"Welke volgorde is correct voor een gestructureerd betoog?",opts:["daarnaast, ten eerste, tot slot, bovendien","tot slot, ten eerste, bovendien, daarnaast","bovendien, tot slot, ten eerste, daarnaast","ten eerste, daarnaast, bovendien, tot slot"],ans:"ten eerste, daarnaast, bovendien, tot slot",hint:"Arguments build from first to final."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["Daarnaast","Tot slot","Tenzij","Naarmate"],hint:"Adding a parallel argument before a stronger one.",s:"{1} bespaar je geld. Bovendien is het goed voor je gezondheid.",a:"Daarnaast"},
        {type:"mc",q:"'Bovendien is er een personeelstekort in de gezondheidszorg.' What does bovendien do here?",opts:["Adds emphasis to a supporting argument","Introduces the first argument","Signals the conclusion","Expresses a condition"],ans:"Adds emphasis to a supporting argument",hint:"Which connector piles on additional evidence forcefully?"},
        {type:"fb",opts:["Tot slot","Ten eerste","Doordat","Mits"],hint:"This signals your final point in the argument.",s:"{1} wil ik benadrukken dat samenwerking essentieel is.",a:"Tot slot"},
        {type:"mc",q:"'Ten eerste... Daarnaast... ___ is er een tekort aan zorgpersoneel.' Which connector fills the blank as the STRONGEST additive signal?",opts:["Daarnaast","Bovendien","Ten eerste","Tot slot"],ans:"Bovendien",hint:"This connector piles on the most forceful additional argument"}
  ]},
  {id:"v2u26l6",title:"Integratie & Identiteit",icon:"🌍",xp:40,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"Integratie & Identiteit",desc:"Bespreek thema's rond integratie, identiteit en diversiteit in de Nederlandse samenleving. Combineer nieuwe woordenschat met de voegwoorden uit eerdere lessen.",goals:["Vocabulaire over integratie en identiteit","Diversiteit en tolerantie bespreken","Maatschappelijke thema's genuanceerd bespreken"]},
        {type:"teach",trg:"de integratie",src:"integration",pos:"noun",gender:"c",phonetic:"in-tuh-GRAH-see",note:"de article. Key concept in Dutch society. Inburgering = civic integration.",example:"A: Hoe verloopt de integratie van nieuwkomers in Nederland?\nB: Dat verschilt enorm per persoon en regio.\nA: De taal leren is een belangrijke stap, toch?\nB: Ja, taal is cruciaal voor integratie.\nA: Hoewel het ook om werk en sociale contacten gaat.\nB: Precies, integratie is een proces van twee kanten.",exampleSrc:"A: How does the integration of newcomers go in the Netherlands?\nB: That differs enormously per person and region.\nA: Learning the language is an important step, right?\nB: Yes, language is crucial for integration.\nA: Although it's also about work and social contacts.\nB: Exactly, integration is a two-way process.",funFact:"Germanic cousin of English 'integration'. Dutch and English are sister languages."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"de identiteit",src:"identity",pos:"noun",gender:"c",phonetic:"ee-den-tee-TITE",note:"de article. Culturele identiteit, nationale identiteit, persoonlijke identiteit.",example:"A: Wat is voor jou je identiteit?\nB: Dat is een lastige vraag. Ik ben veel dingen.\nA: Hoewel je in Nederland woont, voel je je ook verbonden met je roots?\nB: Ja, mijn identiteit is meervoudig.\nA: Naarmate je langer hier woont, verandert je identiteit misschien.\nB: Dat klopt, het is een dynamisch proces.",exampleSrc:"A: What is identity to you?\nB: That's a difficult question. I'm many things.\nA: Although you live in the Netherlands, do you also feel connected to your roots?\nB: Yes, my identity is multiple.\nA: As you live here longer, your identity might change.\nB: That's true, it's a dynamic process.",funFact:"A de-word (common gender). About 2/3 of Dutch nouns use 'de'. All plurals always use 'de'."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"de diversiteit",src:"diversity",pos:"noun",gender:"c",phonetic:"dee-ver-see-TITE",note:"de article. Randstad = Holland's urban agglomeration (Amsterdam, Rotterdam, Den Haag, Utrecht).",example:"A: De diversiteit in de Randstad is enorm.\nB: Ja, je hoort er tientallen talen.\nA: Diversiteit verrijkt de samenleving, vind je niet?\nB: Absoluut, mits er ook verbinding is.\nA: Hoewel er soms spanningen zijn, brengt diversiteit creativiteit.\nB: Bovendien maakt het de stad interessanter.",exampleSrc:"A: The diversity in the Randstad is enormous.\nB: Yes, you hear dozens of languages there.\nA: Diversity enriches society, don't you think?\nB: Absolutely, provided there's also connection.\nA: Although there are sometimes tensions, diversity brings creativity.\nB: Furthermore, it makes the city more interesting.",funFact:"Germanic cousin of English 'diversity'. Dutch and English are sister languages."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"de tolerantie",src:"tolerance",pos:"noun",gender:"c",phonetic:"toh-luh-RAN-see",note:"de article. A core Dutch value, often discussed in public debate.",example:"A: Nederland staat bekend om zijn tolerantie.\nB: Dat klopt, hoewel dat beeld soms genuanceerder ligt.\nA: Hoe bedoel je?\nB: Tolerantie betekent niet altijd acceptatie.\nA: Dat is een belangrijk verschil.\nB: Ja, naarmate de samenleving diverser wordt, wordt tolerantie meer op de proef gesteld.",exampleSrc:"A: The Netherlands is known for its tolerance.\nB: That's true, although that image is sometimes more nuanced.\nA: What do you mean?\nB: Tolerance doesn't always mean acceptance.\nA: That's an important difference.\nB: Yes, as society becomes more diverse, tolerance is put to the test more.",funFact:"Germanic cousin of English 'tolerance'. Dutch and English are sister languages."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"de inburgering",src:"civic integration",pos:"noun",gender:"c",phonetic:"IN-bur-guh-ring",note:"de article. From inburgeren (to integrate into citizenry). Mandatory for non-EU immigrants.",example:"A: De inburgering is verplicht voor nieuwkomers.\nB: Wat houdt dat precies in?\nA: Je leert Nederlands en hoe de samenleving werkt.\nB: Hoewel het intensief is, helpt het enorm.\nA: Mits je gemotiveerd bent, lukt het zeker.\nB: De meeste mensen halen hun inburgeringsexamen.",exampleSrc:"A: Civic integration is mandatory for newcomers.\nB: What does that entail exactly?\nA: You learn Dutch and how society works.\nB: Although it's intensive, it helps enormously.\nA: Provided you're motivated, you'll definitely succeed.\nB: Most people pass their civic integration exam.",funFact:"A de-word (common gender). About 2/3 of Dutch nouns use 'de'. All plurals always use 'de'."},
        {type:"tip",title:"Integratie in Nederland",deepDive:"The Netherlands has a formal civic integration system (inburgering). Newcomers must:\n\n1. Pass Dutch language exams (A2 level minimum)\n2. Learn about Dutch society and values\n3. Complete an orientation on the Dutch labor market\n\nThe system has been reformed multiple times. Current policy emphasizes personal responsibility (eigen verantwoordelijkheid) and earlier language learning.",text:"Key terms for discussing integration in Dutch society:\n\n- inburgering: civic integration (mandatory course for immigrants)\n- nieuwkomer: newcomer\n- Nederlander met migratieachtergrond: person with migration background\n- participatie: participation in society\n- het inburgeringsexamen: civic integration exam"},
        {type:"mc",q:"Welk woord betekent 'tolerance'?",opts:["de tolerantie","de integratie","de diversiteit","de identiteit"],ans:"de tolerantie",hint:"A value the Netherlands is known for internationally."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["diversiteit","tolerantie","identiteit","integratie"],hint:"The variety of people and cultures in a city.",s:"De {1} in de grote steden is enorm; je hoort er tientallen talen.",a:"diversiteit"},
        {type:"mc",q:"'Integratie is een proces van twee kanten.' Wat betekent dit?",opts:["Only newcomers must adapt","Both newcomers and society must make an effort","Only the government is responsible","Integration happens automatically"],ans:"Both newcomers and society must make an effort",hint:"'Van twee kanten' means from two sides."},
        {type:"match",pairs:[
          {trg:"de integratie",src:"integration"},
          {trg:"de identiteit",src:"identity"},
          {trg:"de diversiteit",src:"diversity"},
          {trg:"de tolerantie",src:"tolerance"},
          {trg:"de inburgering",src:"civic integration"}
        ]},
        {type:"fb",opts:["Hoewel","Mits","Doordat","Zodat"],hint:"Acknowledging tolerance while noting tensions exist too.",s:"{1} Nederland tolerant is, zijn er ook spanningen in de samenleving.",a:"Hoewel"},
        {type:"mc",q:"'Naarmate de samenleving diverser wordt, verandert de identiteit van het land.' What relationship does naarmate express?",opts:["A condition","A contradiction","A proportional change","A purpose"],ans:"A proportional change",hint:"As one thing increases, the other ___s accordingly."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Provided courses are good, integration goes better, as diversity increases.",s:"{1} er goede inburgeringscursussen zijn, verloopt de {2} beter, {3} de diversiteit in de samenleving toeneemt.",blanks:{"1":"Mits","2":"integratie","3":"naarmate"},pool:["Mits","integratie","naarmate","tenzij","tolerantie"]},
        {type:"fb",opts:["identiteit","integratie","tolerantie","diversiteit"],hint:"What makes you who you are.",s:"Persoonlijke {1} is een complex begrip dat door veel factoren wordt bepaald.",a:"identiteit"},
        {type:"mc",q:"Welk voegwoord past? '___ nieuwkomers de taal leren, kunnen ze beter participeren.'",opts:["Ofschoon","Hoewel","Tenzij","Naarmate"],ans:"Naarmate",hint:"The more they learn the language, the better they can participate."},
        {type:"mc",q:"'De inburgering is verplicht voor nieuwkomers.' Wat is 'de inburgering'?",opts:["civic integration for newcomers","a type of Dutch food","a holiday celebration","a sports competition"],ans:"civic integration for newcomers",hint:"In + burger (citizen) + ing. Becoming part of the citizenry."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["Naarmate","Tenzij","Mits","Zodat"],hint:"As diversity increases, identity changes proportionally.",s:"{1} de diversiteit toeneemt, verandert ook de identiteit van de samenleving.",a:"Naarmate"}
  ]},
  {id:"v2u26l7",title:"Essays Schrijven",icon:"✍️",xp:40,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"Essays Schrijven",desc:"Leer essayconnectoren voor academisch en professioneel schrijven: desalniettemin, samenvattend, concluderend, enerzijds...anderzijds. Combineer alles wat je hebt geleerd.",goals:["Academische connectoren beheersen","Een gestructureerd essay opbouwen","Tegenstellingen en conclusies formuleren"]},
        {type:"teach",trg:"desalniettemin",src:"nevertheless, nonetheless",pos:"noun",gender:null,note:"Very formal. Acknowledges obstacle, then continues. Written Dutch mostly.",example:"A: De woningmarkt is overspannen.\nB: Desalniettemin blijven mensen kopen.\nA: Hoe kan dat?\nB: Desalniettemin geloven ze dat de prijzen blijven stijgen.\nA: Het is riskant.\nB: Desalniettemin is het voor velen de enige optie.",exampleSrc:"A: The housing market is overheated.\nB: Nevertheless, people keep buying.\nA: How is that possible?\nB: Nonetheless, they believe prices will keep rising.\nA: It's risky.\nB: Nevertheless, for many it's the only option.",funFact:"Dutch and English are the closest major language pair in the world. Many words share common roots."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"samenvattend",src:"in summary, to summarize",pos:"noun",gender:null,note:"Used to wrap up an argument. Often at the start of a concluding paragraph.",example:"A: Je hebt veel argumenten genoemd.\nB: Ja. Samenvattend: de gezondheidszorg heeft drie problemen.\nA: Namelijk?\nB: Samenvattend: te lange wachttijden, te hoge kosten en personeelstekort.\nA: Een heldere samenvatting.\nB: Samenvattend kunnen we zeggen dat hervorming nodig is.",exampleSrc:"A: You've mentioned many arguments.\nB: Yes. In summary: healthcare has three problems.\nA: Namely?\nB: In summary: waiting times too long, costs too high, and staff shortage.\nA: A clear summary.\nB: To summarize, we can say that reform is needed.",funFact:"Dutch and English are the closest major language pair in the world. Many words share common roots."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"concluderend",src:"in conclusion",pos:"noun",gender:null,note:"Signals the final conclusion of an essay or argument. Very formal.",example:"A: We hebben het onderwerp uitgebreid besproken.\nB: Ja. Concluderend denk ik dat er verandering nodig is.\nA: Op welk vlak?\nB: Concluderend: het beleid moet worden aangepast.\nA: Dat is een sterke conclusie.\nB: Concluderend wil ik zeggen dat de burger meer inspraak verdient.",exampleSrc:"A: We've discussed the topic extensively.\nB: Yes. In conclusion, I think change is needed.\nA: In what area?\nB: In conclusion: the policy must be adjusted.\nA: That's a strong conclusion.\nB: In conclusion, I want to say that the citizen deserves more say.",funFact:"Dutch and English are the closest major language pair in the world. Many words share common roots."},
        {type:"teach",trg:"enerzijds...anderzijds",src:"on the one hand...on the other hand",pos:"noun",gender:null,note:"Presents two sides of an argument. Essential for balanced essays.",example:"A: Hoe kijk je tegen de woningmarkt aan?\nB: Enerzijds begrijp ik dat er meer gebouwd moet worden.\nA: En anderzijds?\nB: Anderzijds moeten we ook de natuur beschermen.\nA: Dat is een lastig dilemma.\nB: Ja, enerzijds wil iedereen een huis, anderzijds is de ruimte beperkt.",exampleSrc:"A: How do you view the housing market?\nB: On the one hand, I understand that more needs to be built.\nA: And on the other hand?\nB: On the other hand, we must also protect nature.\nA: That's a difficult dilemma.\nB: Yes, on one hand everyone wants a house, on the other hand space is limited.",funFact:"Dutch and English are the closest major language pair in the world. Many words share common roots."},
        {type:"tip",title:"Essay structuur",deepDive:"Dutch academic writing values:\n\n1. Directheid (directness): State your thesis early\n2. Structuur (structure): Clear paragraph divisions with signal words\n3. Nuance: Acknowledge counterarguments (enerzijds...anderzijds)\n4. Conclusie: Always end with a clear summary\n\nAvoid: emotional language, too many exclamation marks, unsupported claims.",text:"A complete Dutch essay uses these connectors:\n\nInleiding: Ten eerste...\nArgument 2: Daarnaast / Bovendien...\nTegenwicht: Enerzijds...anderzijds / Hoewel...\nNuance: Desalniettemin...\nAfsluiting: Samenvattend / Concluderend...\n\nThis creates a balanced, academic-style argument."},
        {type:"mc",q:"Welk woord betekent 'nevertheless'?",opts:["desalniettemin","samenvattend","concluderend","bovendien"],ans:"desalniettemin",hint:"A very long, formal word that means 'despite all that'."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["Concluderend","Desalniettemin","Enerzijds","Doordat"],hint:"This word signals you're wrapping up with a final conclusion.",s:"{1} kunnen we zeggen dat het onderwijs hervormd moet worden.",a:"Concluderend"},
        {type:"mc",q:"'Enerzijds is fietsen gezond, ___ is het soms gevaarlijk.' What fills the blank?",opts:["desalniettemin","anderzijds","samenvattend","bovendien"],ans:"anderzijds",hint:"The partner of enerzijds, presenting the other side."},
        {type:"match",pairs:[
          {trg:"desalniettemin",src:"nevertheless"},
          {trg:"samenvattend",src:"in summary"},
          {trg:"concluderend",src:"in conclusion"},
          {trg:"enerzijds",src:"on the one hand"},
          {trg:"anderzijds",src:"on the other hand"}
        ]},
        {type:"fb",opts:["Desalniettemin","Doordat","Zodat","Mits"],hint:"Despite disadvantages, you still support it. What bridges that contrast?",s:"Het plan heeft nadelen. {1} steun ik het.",a:"Desalniettemin"},
        {type:"mc",q:"Which word would you use to START the final paragraph of an essay?",opts:["Daarnaast","Ten eerste","Samenvattend","Enerzijds"],ans:"Samenvattend",hint:"You're wrapping everything up in a summary."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"On one hand good, on the other hand problems. Nevertheless, keep improving.",s:"{1} is de gezondheidszorg goed. {2} zijn er lange wachttijden. {3} moeten we het systeem blijven verbeteren.",blanks:{"1":"Enerzijds","2":"Anderzijds","3":"Desalniettemin"},pool:["Enerzijds","Anderzijds","Desalniettemin","Naarmate","Tenzij"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"Welke volgorde is logisch voor een essay?",opts:["Samenvattend, ten eerste, anderzijds, hoewel, bovendien","Concluderend, ten eerste, samenvattend, daarnaast, bovendien","Desalniettemin, tot slot, ten eerste, bovendien, samenvattend","Ten eerste, daarnaast, bovendien, desalniettemin, concluderend"],ans:"Ten eerste, daarnaast, bovendien, desalniettemin, concluderend",hint:"Arguments build up, then nuance, then conclusion."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["Desalniettemin","Samenvattend","Ten eerste","Doordat"],hint:"Despite high costs, the government still invests. What word bridges that contrast?",s:"De kosten zijn hoog. {1} investeert de overheid in verbetering.",a:"Desalniettemin"},
        {type:"mc",q:"'Enerzijds begrijp ik de bezwaren, anderzijds zie ik de voordelen.' This structure shows:",opts:["A balanced view of both sides","Complete agreement","A cause-effect relationship","A chronological sequence"],ans:"A balanced view of both sides",hint:"Enerzijds... ___: the second half of 'on one hand... on the other'"},
        {type:"fb",opts:["Desalniettemin","Doordat","Zodat","Ten eerste"],hint:"Despite big problems, there is hope. What word bridges that contrast?",s:"De problemen zijn groot. {1} is er hoop voor de toekomst.",a:"Desalniettemin"},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"As education improves, opportunities become greater. That's the consequence of good policy.",s:"{1} het onderwijs verbetert, {2} de kansen voor jongeren groter. Dat is het {3} van goed beleid.",blanks:{"1":"Naarmate","2":"worden","3":"gevolg"},pool:["Naarmate","worden","gevolg","Hoewel","oorzaak"]}
  ]},
  {id:"v2u26l8",title:"Debat over Nederland",icon:"🇳🇱",xp:50,board:true,steps:[
        {type:"intro",title:"Debat over Nederland",desc:"Een allesomvattende les waarin je alle voegwoorden, signaalwoorden en maatschappelijke thema's combineert in een debat over de Nederlandse samenleving.",goals:["Alle voegwoorden uit deze unit combineren","Gestructureerd debatteren","Complexe zinnen bouwen over maatschappelijke thema's"]},
        {type:"tip",title:"Debatteren in het Nederlands",deepDive:"Dutch debate culture values:\n\n- Polderen: finding consensus through discussion\n- Directheid: being straightforward about your views\n- Nuance: acknowledging complexity\n- Feiten: basing arguments on facts, not emotions\n\nUseful debate phrases:\nIk ben van mening dat... (I am of the opinion that...)\nDaar ben ik het niet mee eens. (I don't agree with that.)\nKun je dat onderbouwen? (Can you support that?)",text:"In a Dutch debate, structure your argument:\n\n1. Standpunt: State your position clearly\n2. Argumenten: Ten eerste... daarnaast... bovendien...\n3. Nuance: Hoewel... enerzijds... anderzijds...\n4. Voorwaarden: Mits... tenzij...\n5. Conclusie: Samenvattend... concluderend...\n\nUse doordat/zodat for cause/result, naarmate/hoe...hoe for trends."},
        {type:"mc",q:"'___ de bevolking vergrijst, stijgen de zorgkosten des te sneller.' Welk voegwoord?",opts:["Naarmate","Hoewel","Mits","Tenzij"],ans:"Naarmate",hint:"As one trend increases, another follows proportionally."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["Mits","Hoewel","Doordat","Naarmate"],hint:"The benefit depends on a condition being met.",s:"{1} de overheid investeert in onderwijs, zal de samenleving ervan profiteren.",a:"Mits"},
        {type:"mc",q:"'Hoewel de diversiteit soms tot spanningen leidt, ___ verrijkt zij de samenleving.' What fills the blank?",opts:["doordat","desalniettemin","zodat","mits"],ans:"desalniettemin",hint:"Despite tensions, diversity still enriches. What word bridges that?"},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"On one hand quality, on the other hand waiting times. In conclusion, improve.",s:"{1} is de Nederlandse gezondheidszorg van hoge kwaliteit. {2} zijn de wachttijden soms te lang. {3} moeten we het systeem blijven verbeteren.",blanks:{"1":"Enerzijds","2":"Anderzijds","3":"Concluderend"},pool:["Enerzijds","Anderzijds","Concluderend","Naarmate","Tenzij"]},
        {type:"fb",opts:["Naarmate","Tenzij","Mits","Hoewel"],hint:"As more houses are built, the market stabilizes proportionally.",s:"{1} er meer woningen gebouwd worden, wordt de woningmarkt stabieler.",a:"Naarmate"},
        {type:"mc",q:"Welke zin combineert doordat en zodat correct?",opts:["Doordat zodat de overheid investeerde, studeerden jongeren.","Zodat de overheid investeerde, doordat het onderwijs verbeterde.","Doordat de overheid investeerde, verbeterde het onderwijs, zodat meer jongeren konden studeren.","Mits doordat de overheid investeerde, zodat jongeren studeerden."],ans:"Doordat de overheid investeerde, verbeterde het onderwijs, zodat meer jongeren konden studeren.",hint:"First the cause (___), then the result leading to a purpose (___)."},
        {type:"match",pairs:[
          {trg:"doordat",src:"because of the fact that"},
          {trg:"zodat",src:"so that"},
          {trg:"mits",src:"provided that"},
          {trg:"tenzij",src:"unless"},
          {trg:"hoewel",src:"although"},
          {trg:"naarmate",src:"as / the more that"}
        ]},
        {type:"fb",opts:["Daarnaast","Tenzij","Doordat","Concluderend"],hint:"Adding a parallel argument after the first one.",s:"Ten eerste is tolerantie belangrijk. {1} moeten we diversiteit omarmen.",a:"Daarnaast"},
        {type:"mc",q:"'___ het integratiebeleid verbeterd wordt, zullen nieuwkomers beter participeren.' Welk voegwoord drukt een voorwaarde uit?",opts:["Naarmate","Doordat","Hoewel","Mits"],ans:"Mits",hint:"The improvement of integration policy is a condition for better participation."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"First education, additionally housing, in conclusion the government must act.",s:"{1} eerste moet het {2} beter. {3} moeten er meer woningen komen. {4} wil ik zeggen dat de {5} verantwoordelijkheid moet nemen.",blanks:{"1":"Ten","2":"onderwijs","3":"Daarnaast","4":"Concluderend","5":"overheid"},pool:["Ten","onderwijs","Daarnaast","Concluderend","overheid","Hoewel","beleid"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"'Ofschoon er kritiek is op het beleid, blijft Nederland desalniettemin hoog scoren op leefbaarheid.' Welke twee functies hebben ofschoon en desalniettemin?",opts:["concession and contrast","cause and result","condition and purpose","proportion and comparison"],ans:"concession and contrast",hint:"Ofschoon acknowledges criticism, ___ asserts a positive outcome."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"Although it's difficult, I don't give up, so that I reach my goal.",s:"{1} het soms moeilijk is, geef ik niet op, {2} ik mijn doel wil bereiken.",blanks:{"1":"Hoewel","2":"zodat"},pool:["Hoewel","zodat","doordat","mits"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"Welk signaalwoord gebruik je om een essay af te sluiten?",opts:["Ten eerste","Samenvattend","Daarnaast","Enerzijds"],ans:"Samenvattend",hint:"You're wrapping up all your arguments into a final summary."},
        {type:"drag_fill",hint:"As society diversifies, integration issues grow. Provided there's dialogue, we solve problems together.",s:"{1} de samenleving diverser wordt, worden vraagstukken rond {2} complexer. {3} er goede dialoog is, kunnen we {4} samen oplossen.",blanks:{"1":"Naarmate","2":"integratie","3":"Mits","4":"problemen"},pool:["Naarmate","integratie","Mits","problemen","Hoewel","tolerantie"]},
        {type:"mc",q:"Je schrijft een essay over de woningmarkt. Wat is de beste openingszin?",opts:["Desalniettemin zijn de huizenprijzen hoog.","Samenvattend is de woningmarkt een probleem.","Ten eerste wil ik beargumenteren dat de woningmarkt hervormd moet worden.","Anderzijds moeten er meer huizen komen."],ans:"Ten eerste wil ik beargumenteren dat de woningmarkt hervormd moet worden.",hint:"An essay opens with the first argument, not a summary or contrast."},
        {type:"fb",opts:["Hoe","Naarmate","Doordat","Mits"],hint:"Proportional structure: both halves start the same way (the more...the more)",s:"{1} meer mensen de taal leren, des te beter de integratie verloopt.",a:"Hoe"},
        {type:"mc",q:"Which conjunction introduces a NEGATIVE exception?",opts:["doordat","mits","hoewel","tenzij"],ans:"tenzij",hint:"UNLESS: the exception that cancels the plan."}
  ]}
]};
